d  Commencement Parking will be allowed on the Parade Ground  weather permitting  for all activities  Please pay attention to the traffic pattern for the departure of cadets after Commencement   The area in front of Barracks will be congested with all of the cadets trying to depart at the same time  Vehicles should remain parked on the Parade Ground  when possible  and the cadet s belongings carried to the vehicle   The VMI Police need your assistance and patience to ensure that the cadet departure is accomplished in the quickest and safest manner possible  Inclement Weather Parking If heavy rain makes parking on the Parade Ground impractical  the following parking options are available  Satellite parking will be available in the Lowe s lower parking lot  next to WalMart  a shuttle service will be provided from the parking lot to Cameron Hall  Additional parking may be found throughout post in permanent parking areas    On Post   At VMI Parking is available on a first come  first served basis  Once on Post parking is filled  you are asked to proceed to the off Post parking locations described below and use the shuttle services provided    Parking in Walking Distance Other City Parking  On weekends  there are no time limits for parking on the street or in city parking lots    Contact the Lexington Visitor Center for more information  Satellite Shuttle Parking Shuttle service will run during posted periods when satellite parking is used  Signage will be placed at the following locations when they are being used  The satellite parking is located at Lowe s on Rt  11 in Lexington  next to the WalMart  Parking will be available at Lowe s from 7 a m  to 5 p m  on May 15 and from 7 a m  to 5 p m  on May 16  Shuttle service will be provided continuously between this location and Post during these periods starting at 7 30 a m  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non